## Delimiter: ","
## chr    (3): Version, VCF0900c, VCF0901b
## dbl (1019): VCF0004, VCF0006, VCF0006a, VCF0009x, VCF0010x, VCF0011x, VCF000...

## â„¹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## â„¹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
anes_optimism <- data.frame(anes_full$VCF0004, anes_full$VCF0302, anes_full$VCF0872, anes_full$VCF0881, anes_full$VCF9244, anes_full$VCF9245)
anes_optimism <- na.omit(anes_optimism)
anes_optimism <- anes_optimism %>%
  rename(year = anes_full.VCF0004, party = anes_full.VCF0302, economy_next_year = anes_full.VCF0872, personal_next_year = anes_full.VCF0881, can_trust_people = anes_full.VCF9244, satisfied_with_life = anes_full.VCF9245)
anes_optimism <- subset(anes_optimism, anes_optimism$economy_next_year <= 5 & anes_optimism$personal_next_year <= 5 & anes_optimism$can_trust_people >= 1 & anes_optimism$satisfied_with_life >= 1 & anes_optimism$party <= 5)
anes_optimism <- subset(anes_optimism, anes_optimism$party == 1 | anes_optimism$party == 5)
anes_optimism$party <- recode(anes_optimism$party, "1" = "R", "5" = "D")

anes_optimism$economy_next_year <- recode(anes_optimism$economy_next_year, "5" = 0, "3" = 5, "1" = 10)

anes_optimism$personal_next_year <- recode(anes_optimism$personal_next_year, "1" = 10, "2" = 5, "3" = 0)

anes_optimism$can_trust_people <- recode(anes_optimism$can_trust_people, "1" = 10, "2" = 7.5, "3" = 5, "4" = 2.5, "5" = 0)

anes_optimism$satisfied_with_life <- recode(anes_optimism$satisfied_with_life, "1" = 10, "2" = 7.5, "3" = 5, "4" = 2.5, "5" = 0)
anes_optimism <- anes_optimism %>%
  group_by(year, party) %>%
  summarise(mean_econ = mean(economy_next_year), mean_personal = mean(personal_next_year), mean_trust = mean(can_trust_people), mean_satisfaction = mean(satisfied_with_life))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
ggplot(anes_optimism, aes(x=year, y=mean_econ, color=party)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) +
  ggtitle("Confidence in Next Year's Economy by Party") +
  xlab("Year") +
  ylab("Confidence in Economy") +
  scale_x_binned(name = waiver())

ggplot(anes_optimism, aes(x=year, y=mean_personal, color=party)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) +
  ggtitle("Confidence in Personal Financial Situation Next Year by Party") +
  xlab("Year") +
  ylab("Confidence in Personal Financial Situation") +
  scale_x_binned(name = waiver())

ggplot(anes_optimism, aes(x=year, y=mean_trust, color=party)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) +
  ggtitle("Trust in Other People by Party") +
  xlab("Year") +
  ylab("Trust in Others") +
  scale_x_binned(name = waiver())

ggplot(anes_optimism, aes(x=year, y=mean_satisfaction, color=party)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("blue", "red")) +
  ggtitle("Satisfaction with Life by Party") +
  xlab("Year") +
  ylab("Satisfaction with Life") +
  scale_x_binned(name = waiver())
